&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you have experience in the role of continuing care/facilitating an effective discharge of long term patients and improving discharge planning?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Anopportunity has arisen to become theContinuingCare Co-ordinator withinPaediatric Critical Care here at the Children’s Hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will be expected to lead the discharge process of children with complex health needs/long term ventilatory needs into the community. Work as a role model for all staff and being an expert in communication with families and the multidisciplinary team is essential. Along with working alongside the Trust&#39;s Complex Care Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience in other aspects of Nurse Management would ideally include Sickness Management, PDR, Conflict Management and Resolution and performing interviews.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sheffield Children’s NHS Foundation trust hosts Embrace, the only Paediatric/ Neonatal transport service within the British Isles and PCCU work closely with this team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information or an informal visit please contact Angela Hughes, Lead Nurse, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;angela.hughes20@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
